{
  "rationale": "Supervisor is structured into (1) marker tracking/approach with move_to_marker, (2) search/scan with full_rotate and short exploration commits, and (3) obstacle recovery that never returns directly to move_forward after obstacle_front. Marker_close is treated as a terminal goal where stop is the only controllable. Uncontrollable events are fully covered per state with safe self-loops in commit/scan/recovery states to prevent preemption, while safety-critical obstacle_* events force recovery/escape.",
