  "strategy": [
    "If marker_close occurs in any state, transition to goal_stop where stop is the only effective behavior.",
    "When marker_seen occurs in clear/search states, switch to marker_track/marker_approach and use move_to_marker as the primary controllable.",
    "If marker_lost occurs during tracking, immediately go to scan_full to reacquire rather than continuing blind approach.",
    "Obstacle_front triggers recover_back (escape) and then scan_full before resuming exploration; never returns directly to move_forward after obstacle_front.",
    "Obstacle_left prefers clockwise recovery (recover_rotate_cw); obstacle_right prefers counterclockwise recovery (recover_rotate_ccw) to reduce oscillations.",
    "Commit/scan/recovery states self-loop on non-critical uncontrollables (path_clear/marker_seen/marker_lost) so the intended one-shot controllable completes without being preempted."
  ]
